column5: Welcome to Barrie.  I've lived here a couple of years and its a great place to be.  Can't say I've heard of a 19" perch though.
So you took a bunch of pics of a buncha houses and some broad, but no pics of a 19" perch? Bull.
...and marked some lakers down to 150' eh, either you were doing a low level fly past or someones been dredging Kempenfelt Bay, deepest sounding on any map I've seen is 136 feet.   dooda dooda...
I think we all need a pic of this 19" perch!!!
interesting post whats with the wicked weasel?

wow a 19 inch perch thats nearly 4 inches longer than the ontario record.   Yellow Perch Angler Information Record Information Name:  Dave Leslie Weight: 2.42 lbs. Hometown: Long Beach Length: 15.13 in. Waterbody: Lake Erie Girth: 12.13 in. Bait/Lure: Minnow Date Caught: March 20, 2003  (TAKEN FROM THE ONTARIO FEDERATION OF ANGLERS AND HUNTERS WEBSITE)  show us a pic if you want us to believe it!!  keep it reel.  jason
Now, now, don't be insulting nature, weasels are a pretty sharp looking animal compared to that ....yuck
